    <section id="story" class="section">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2>Our Story</h2>
        <p>
          This project started with a simple challenge: could we redesign Arngren in a way that feels
          modern and user-friendly, but still respects the original “everything everywhere” vibe of the site?
        </p>
        <p>
          We focused on creating clear sections, readable text, and a layout that works on laptops and phones.
          Our goal was to keep the energy of the original, but remove the confusion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="redesign" class="section section-alt">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2>What We Redesigned</h2>
        <ul class="redesign-list">
          <li><strong>Sign In / Sign Up Flow:</strong> Clean, centered blocks with clear calls to tell you where you’re supposed to go.</li>
          <li><strong>Visual Hierarchy:</strong> Big headings, readable text, and simplified content blocks.</li>
          <li><strong>Consistent Styling:</strong> We have a general theme, buttons, and form fields.</li>
          <li><strong>Responsive Layout:</strong> Pages that look good on both desktop and mobile screens. We also removed most of the clutter from the website.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

